        "text": "Based on DOL National Database of Childcare Prices data, states in the South and rural Midwest consistently rank as the most affordable. Mississippi, Alabama, Arkansas, South Dakota, and Oklahoma typically have the lowest median annual childcare costs for infants, often below $7,000 per year for center-based care."
