        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">How does childcare cost compare to rent in different states?</summary>
        <p>In the most expensive states, annual infant center care can exceed annual rent for a one-bedroom apartment. In the cheapest states, childcare typically represents 10–15% of median household income, versus 20–35% in high-cost states.</p>
      </details>
